20kg and weighs about The panel is reusable and adjustable to fit securely within doorways ranging from 0.78m to 1.1m An extendable panel with an inflatable seal that provides temporary flood protection 0.6m QUICK AND SIMPLE INSTALLATI­ON WITHOUT TOOLS The panel is positioned across the doorway. A lever is used to extend the side panels until it touches the door frame. A pump is then activated to inflate a watertight seal around the panel. 2 3 1 Close-up of the watertight seal PORTABLE FLOOD BARRIER (PFB) A self-anchoring flood barrier that, when installed, creates a 0.5mhigh dam which helps divert flood water away from an area or contain them. No tools are needed for A complete set of installati­on and the sections PFB extends about
6m can be stacked to minimise the storage space needed and for ease of transporta­tion. in length. Lightweigh­t and designed for use on firm surfaces such as roads and pavements. Average human height: 1.7m 0.5m Damming
• The rear wall dams the flood water.
The water ’s pressure is absorbed by several large bulges, which also act as drainage channels. The barriers interlock with one another via a locking mechanism. Anchoring
• The anchoring force is proportion­al to the difference in water pressure between the upper and lower side of the boxwall.
• A system of drainage channels on the lower side diverts leaking water, so that no counter-pressure arises. Source: PUB ST PHOTOS: LIM K AILI, MARK CHEONG STRAITS TIMES GRAPHICS The base section of the boxwall is pressed firmly against the ground by the weight of the flood water. There is a pair of cellular rubber soles on the underside to provide a strong grip on the road. Sealing
Below the front edge is a sealing strip made of cellular rubber. This keeps the leakage of water at the bottom to a minimum. •
